lass=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 03, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104oud1665702693770.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/oud1665702693770.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/oud1665702693770.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"oud1665702693770\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"oud1665702693770__uoprprms_406729\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Return the number of parameters in the specified operation.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"oud1665702693770__topic_d122687e1_d122688e1_d122689e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104oud1665702693770_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"oud1665702693770__codeblock_ghn_sg2_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">int uoprprms (UHACT hOpr, long* pNum);</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"oud1665702693770__topic_d86827e1_d86828e1_d86829e1_d86830e1_d86831e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d262532e61\">Parameters</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"oud1665702693770__parml_owg_5g2_bwb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">hOpr</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">The handle to the operation, as returned by <code class=\"ph codeph\">uinstopr</code></dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">pNum</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">(Output) The number of parameters in the operation</dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"oud1665702693770__topic_d86832e1_d86833e1_d86834e1_d86835e1_d86836e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d262532e92\">Return Values</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oud1665702693770__d5955e20\">For more information, see the \"Call-In API Return\n        Codes\" topic.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"oud1665702693770__topic_d86837e1_d86838e1_d86839e1_d86840e1_d86841e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d262532e101\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oud1665702693770__d5956e20\">Library:  <span class=\"ph filepath\">ucall</span></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"oud1665702693770__topic_d86842e1_d86843e1_d86844e1_d86845e1_d86846e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d262532e113\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oud1665702693770__p_d122717e1_d122718e1_d122719e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uoprprms</code> returns the number of\n            parameters in the operation identified by <var class=\"keyword varname\">hOpr</var>. This is useful if you\n            want to loop through all the parameters, examining them one-by-one. You can use the\n            functions <code class=\"ph codeph\">uprmdir</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">uprmtype</code>, and\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">uniname</code> to get information about a specific parameter. This makes it\n            possible to dynamically call Uniface operations.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"oud1665702693770__section_ucw_zg2_bwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d262532e136\">Example: uoprprms, uniname, uprmdir, and uprmtype</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following routine prints out a list of the parameters of an arbitrary\n            operation in an arbitrary component.</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104oud1665702693770_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"oud1665702693770__codeblock_odj_bh2_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">#include &lt;h3gl.h&gt;\n\nchar *types[] = { \"Unknown\", \"String\", \"Boolean\", \"Numeric\", \"Float\", \"Date\", \"Time\",\n\"DateTime\",\"LinearDate\", \"LinearTime\", \"LinearDateTime\", \"Raw\", \"Image\", \"Entity\",\n\"Occurrence\", \"IncludedEntity\", \"Handle\" };\nchar *dires[] = { \"Unknown\", \"In\", \"Out\", \"InOut\" };\n\nvoid inspect_operation_params (char *svcname, char *oprname)\n{\nUHACT hEnv, hIn, hOp, hParm;\nlong i, nParams;\nint pType, pDir;\nchar name[1+UPRMNAMESIZE];\nchar* template1 = \" %3s %-20s %-20s %s\\n\";\nchar* template2 = \" %3d %-20s %-20s %s\\n\";\n\nueopen(&amp;hEnv);\nuinstnew(hEnv, (UCHAR*)svcname, 0, 0, UDEFAULT_COMM_MODE, 0, &amp;hIn, 0);\nuinstopr(hIn, (UCHAR*)oprname, 0, &amp;hOp);\nprintf(\"Parameters of operation %s in service %s:\\n\\n\", oprname, svcname);\nprintf(template1, \"Num\", \"Name \", \"Type \",\n\"Direction\");\nprintf(template1, \"===\", \"====================\", \"====================\",\n\"=========\");\n\nuoprprms(hOp, &amp;nParams);\nfor ( i=1; i&lt;=nParams; i++ )\n{\nuprmdir(hOp, i, &amp;pDir);\nuprmgeth(hOp, i, 0, &amp;hParm);\nuprmtype(hParm, &amp;pType);\nuniname(hOp, i, UPRMNAMESIZE, name);\n\nprintf(template2, i, name, types[pType], dires[pDir]);\n}\nprintf(\"\\n\");\n\nuinstdel(hIn, 0);\nufreeh(&amp;hOp);\nufreeh(&amp;hIn);\nufreeh(&amp;hEnv);\n}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">Here is an example of output generated by this function:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104oud1665702693770_html_2\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"oud1665702693770__codeblock_rh3_dh2_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">Parameters of operation MYOP in service TESTSVC:\n\nNum Name Type Direction\n=== ==================== ==================== =========\n1 P1 Numeric In\n2 P2 String InOut\n3 P3 Date Out</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jhh1665702691902.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Call-In API Return Codes</a><p>Codes that can possibly be returned by functions from the 3GL call-in API are consistent with the values returned by the ProcScript function $procerror, unless noted otherwise.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ajt1665702693842.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>uprmdir</a><p>Return the direction (in/out/inout) of the specified parameter.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pdl1665702693580.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>uprmgeth</a><p>Get the handle of the specified operation parameter or entity field. Or detach a parameter from an operation.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hcs1665702693913.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>uprmtype</a><p>Return the data type of the specified parameter or entity field.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530735\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530735\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "uoprprms Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 03, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Return the number of parameters in the specified operation. Explain this code int uoprprms (UHACT hOpr, long* pNum); Copy Parameters hOpr The handle to the operation, as returned by uinstopr pNum (Output) The number of parameters in the operation Return Values For more information, see the \"Call-In API Return Codes\" topic. Use Library: ucall Description uoprprms returns the number of parameters in the operation identified by hOpr . This is useful if you want to loop through all the parameters, examining them one-by-one. You can use the functions uprmdir , uprmtype , and uniname to get information about a specific parameter. This makes it possible to dynamically call Uniface operations. Example: uoprprms, uniname, uprmdir, and uprmtype The following routine prints out a list of the parameters of an arbitrary operation in an arbitrary component. Explain this code #include <h3gl.h> char *types[] = { \"Unknown\", \"String\", \"Boolean\", \"Numeric\", \"Float\", \"Date\", \"Time\", \"DateTime\",\"LinearDate\", \"LinearTime\", \"LinearDateTime\", \"Raw\", \"Image\", \"Entity\", \"Occurrence\", \"IncludedEntity\", \"Handle\" }; char *dires[] = { \"Unknown\", \"In\", \"Out\", \"InOut\" }; void inspect_operation_params (char *svcname, char *oprname) { UHACT hEnv, hIn, hOp, hParm; long i, nParams; int pType, pDir; char name[1+UPRMNAMESIZE]; char* template1 = \" %3s %-20s %-20s %s\\n\"; char* template2 = \" %3d %-20s %-20s %s\\n\"; ueopen(&hEnv); uinstnew(hEnv, (UCHAR*)svcname, 0, 0, UDEFAULT_COMM_MODE, 0, &hIn, 0); uinstopr(hIn, (UCHAR*)oprname, 0, &hOp); printf(\"Parameters of operation %s in service %s:\\n\\n\", oprname, svcname); printf(template1, \"Num\", \"Name \", \"Type \", \"Direction\"); printf(template1, \"===\", \"====================\", \"====================\", \"=========\"); uoprprms(hOp, &nParams); for ( i=1; i<=nParams; i++ ) { uprmdir(hOp, i, &pDir); uprmgeth(hOp, i, 0, &hParm); uprmtype(hParm, &pType); uniname(hOp, i, UPRMNAMESIZE, name); printf(template2, i, name, types[pType], dires[pDir]); } printf(\"\\n\"); uinstdel(hIn, 0); ufreeh(&hOp); ufreeh(&hIn); ufreeh(&hEnv); } Copy Here is an example of output generated by this function: Explain this code Parameters of operation MYOP in service TESTSVC: Num Name Type Direction === ==================== ==================== ========= 1 P1 Numeric In 2 P2 String InOut 3 P3 Date Out Copy Related Links Call-In API Return Codes Codes that can possibly be returned by functions from the 3GL call-in API are consistent with the values returned by the ProcScript function $procerror, unless noted otherwise. uprmdir Return the direction (in/out/inout) of the specified parameter. uprmgeth Get the handle of the specified operation parameter or entity field. Or detach a parameter from an operation. uprmtype Return the data type of the specified parameter or entity field. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}